The Dredge is one of 37 Killers currently featured in Dead by Daylight.

It was introduced as the Killer of CHAPTER 24: Roots of Dread, a Chapter DLC released on 7 June 2022 and retired on 14 May 2024.

It is still available in the In-Game Store and as part of the Endless Hunt Pack Chapter Pack DLC.

Overview[]

A twisted abomination too disturbing to bear, The Dredge’s malevolence is palpable. All light slowly drains in its presence, surrounding Survivors in darkness. Using lockers as map-wide gateways, it can emerge at any moment, seemingly everywhere at once.

The Dredge is a manifestation of the dark thoughts of a once-vibrant community, able to teleport between Lockers and summon an overwhelming darkness.

Its personal Perks, Dissolution , Darkness Revealed , and Septic Touch , allow it to destroy Pallets, spot Survivors near Lockers, and afflict healing Survivors with Blindness and Exhausted.

Difficulty Rating: Moderate

(These Killers require the Player to be comfortable with the basics of the role, though they share common mechanics with easier ones)

Lore[]

The Fold was founded on a private American island in the 1960s by a group of anonymous philanthropists. Their goal was to establish a peaceful society free of dark thoughts and emotions, attracting the dismayed, disenchanted, and disillusioned from all over the country.

This peace-loving community thrived over the years, and members freely followed the dictates of its charismatic leader Otto Stamper who taught his followers the secret of maintaining happiness through joy-talk, meditation, and the endless reciting of 'good-thinking' mantras.

But not all was bliss within The Fold, and Otto swiftly banished anyone who confessed to having dark thoughts or speaking dark words. Those he appointed as guardians of The Fold were quick to root out malcontents, banishing anyone who thought or spoke against the almost perfect community he had established.

Life was more or less a Utopian dream on the island. Until, that is, the darkness began to slowly leak through the cracks of their spiritual dam and members began to mysteriously disappear.

It wasn't long before fear closed its septic jaws on the island and refused to let go.

The once happy community now gathered in a few homes chanting all the 'good-thinking' mantras in a desperate attempt to rid their lives of this formless creature that seemed to stalk them in the shadows and consume them in their sleep.

Otto tried to quell his followers, telling them that there were malcontents among their ranks and that they alone had summoned the Druanee to their Garden of Joy.

As The Fold bleated fear, Otto evoked desperate measures. Ottomarians were restricted to their homes to prevent the spread of rumours and dark-talk while sleep was forbidden to prevent anyone from releasing dark dreams into the world. Freedom and sleep would return just as soon as the Druanee was no longer upon them.

But when Ottomarians continued to disappear, Otto assembled his followers near the beach where he placed a screaming woman on a wooden stage. There, in the rain, Otto explained to his drenched, alienated, and sleep-deprived congregation that the woman was a journalist here to destroy everything they had created.

As the guardians held the trembling woman, she screamed that Otto wasn't the savior he claimed to be. He belonged to an ancient cult, an exclusive club of billionaires that took pleasure in corrupting and sacrificing people, towns and even countries to an Elder God. The journalist told them Otto hadn't banished anyone! He had tortured and sacrificed them and that they would all be next.

Without hesitation, Otto slit her throat before she could continue to spread lies. As she collapsed to her knees with her hands clasped around her neck, he told his confused and terrified herd that she was working with others within their ranks and that they needed to find the impostors before the Druanee came for them all.

Otto's words shot over the congregation and reached into the murky recesses of their hearts and dredged up dark and fearful things.

Years of suppressed emotions began to bubble up as a thick fog pushed through restless legs and feet. Whispers began, and the whispers became panicked mantras, and the mantras became screams and curses as each member accused the next of malthinking and malspeaking.

Over the howling wind and pounding rain, the screams and curses grew louder and louder as everyone desperately tried to contain the darkness within. But the harder they tried, the quicker they ailed, and within moments the dam burst to release a torrent of hell.

Otto watched his once blissful and joyful herd suddenly erupt into violence unlike anything he had ever seen before. The Fold bleated accusations and tore each other to bits and pieces with hands and teeth and never once did they look up to see their kind and charismatic shepherd smiling down upon them with eyes that were cold, bleak and without pity.

When it was all over, Otto felt the creaking, wooden stage shake as a murder of crows circled above. Suddenly, the ground rose and then sank into a thick, oozing black mud like molasses. Moments later, a formless mass squelched out of the muck and rose like a rearing horse to feed upon the writhing mass of butchered humanity.

It was everywhere and nowhere at once as it slowly picked its way through the carnage, absorbing the darkness, savouring the misery, trailing terrible noises. Shrieks. Cries. Whimpers. Pops. Cracks.

Feasting sounds.

Death sounds.

Dark sounds.

Otto watched the creature as it slowly began to manifest into the very thing he had imagined—the very thing he had made them all imagine.

It turned slowly to look at Otto for a long silent moment, then the Druanee trudged away through the thick black sludge, disappearing into the shadows from which it had come.

Load-out[]

Unique Perks[]

The Dredge comes with 3 Perks that are unique to it:

Darkness Revealed In your presence, places once thought to be safe are perhaps the most dangerous.

Searching a Locker has the following effect:

The Auras of Survivors within 8 metres of any Locker are revealed to you for 6/7/8 seconds.

Darkness Revealed has a cool-down of 30 seconds.

"Stay in the light, my children. In darkness, your fear will expose you." — Otto Stamper

Dissolution Everything turns to dust. It is as inescapable as the coming of the night.

After 3 seconds of injuring a Survivor by any means, Dissolution activates for 12/16/20 seconds:

Instantly breaks the next Pallet that Survivor performs a Fast Vault across while inside your Terror Radius .

"The Garden shall be a place of perfect Joy; through Joy, nothing shall stand in our way." — Otto Stamper Septic Touch The Land of the Shadows subsumes all. Healing only delays the inevitable.

Whenever a Survivor performs a Healing action while they are inside your Terror Radius , that Survivor suffers from the Blindness and Exhausted Status Effects

These effects linger for 6/8/10 seconds after the Healing action is interrupted by any means.

"Do not admit to fear, or pain, or doubt. These are the seeds from which darkness grows." — Otto Stamper

Prestige[]

Prestiging The Dredge will automatically add Tier I of its Unique Perks to the inventories of all other Killers and unlock the ability for their higher-tiered versions to spawn in their Bloodweb .

Prestige The Dredge twice more to automatically add Tier II and Tier III respectively into the other Killers' inventories.

Weapon: Knotted Appendage[]

The Knotted Appendage is the Primary Weapon of The Dredge.

Some of the body parts formed into a crude and horrifying weapon.

Power: Reign of Darkness[]

Power Trivia[]

Movement Speeds:

Main Article

Charging/Holding Reign of Darkness: 3.8 m/s

Walking: 4.6 m/s

Teleportation speed during Daytime: 19 m/s

Teleportation speed during Nightfall: 38 m/s

Gloaming Ability:

Initial Charge time: 10 seconds

This refers to how long it takes for the Power to become available after loading into a Trial.

Cool-down time during Daytime: 10 seconds

Cool-down time during Nightfall: 4 seconds

Activation time: 0.5 seconds

Fade-in / Fade-out time for Remnant: 0.25 seconds

Grabbing Survivor in teleported-to Locker: 3 seconds

Restrictions:

Minimum distance to hooked Survivors: 12 metres

Minimum distance to Locker: 3 metres

Lockers:

Exit Locked Locker duration: 2.25 seconds

Inside Locker FOV: 120 °

Killer Instinct radius during Nightfall: 16 metres

Killer Instinct Linger duration: 3 seconds

Warning Sound threshold: 8 seconds

This refers to how long The Dredge can hide in a Locker before the warning sound triggers.

Prevent Locker-Search cool-down: 1.25 seconds

Nightfall Activation:

Activation threshold: 300 Charges

This refers to how many Charges must be accumulated for Nightfall to start.

Automatic Charge rate: 0.25 c/s

Nightfall automatically charges at this default rate during Daytime.

The value can be increased by The Dredge in various ways, accelerating the progression towards Nightfall:

Hiding inside a Locker adds +6 c/s

Each injured Survivors adds a stack-able +0.75 c/s each for a maximum of:

+1 c/s for 1 injured Survivor.

+2 c/s for 2 injured Survivors.

+3 c/s for 3 injured Survivors.

+4 c/s for 4 injured Survivors.

Injuring a Survivor with a Basic Attack adds +20 Charges

Hooking a Survivor adds +20 Charges

Teleporting back to the Remnant adds +10 Charges

Imminent Nightfall Warning threshold: 85 % charged

This refers to the percentage Nightfall must be charged to when it gives a global sound cue warning to all Players that Nightfall is imminent.

Transition time from Daytime to Nightfall: 3 seconds

Nightfall Discharging:

Discharging threshold: 60 Charges

This refers to how many Charges must be discharged in order for Nightfall to end.

Discharge rate: -1 c/s

Transition time from Nightfall to Daytime: 1.5 seconds

Nightfall VFX:

During Nightfall, to counteract the darkness, the Survivors show special visual effects on their model, akin to an Aura, which cannot be read through objects, however.

This effect has the following requirements for it to be seen:

Survivor to other Survivor: up to 54 metres

Killer to Survivors: up to 20 metres

Locker Priorities[]

When teleporting to a pair of Lockers, there is a distinct hierarchy The Dredge follows when choosing which of the two Lockers it will teleport into:

The Locker a Survivor is either hiding in or interacting with (i.e. locking).

The Locker that is locked (in case of just one of them being locked).

Any of the two Lockers if both have the same state (i.e. both are either unlocked or locked).

Worry Stone While the Ottomarians were told to think only positive thoughts, some kept these stones in their pockets to rub when negative thoughts arose.

The Auras of Survivors locking a Locker are revealed to you for 6 seconds.

Boat Key Only one boat allowed people on and off the island, and the keys were hidden away to prevent deserters.

Increases your Teleportation speed during Daytime by +5 m/s.

Causes all active Locks on Lockers to break once the Exit Gates are powered by any means.

Field Recorder Haddie documented all of her forays near Overlaps, to prove not only to the world but herself what she saw and felt.

Causes the Trial to start in Nightfall.

Causes Nightfall to activate automatically once the last Generator is completed.

Survivors suffer from the Exhausted Status Effect for 15 seconds after coming into contact with the Remnant.

Lavalier Microphone She kept a lavalier mic nearby, allowing her to record her innermost feelings when under great stress.

The Auras of all Survivors are revealed to you for 3 seconds after consuming the last Power Token.

Causes all Lockers within 6 metres of Survivors to open and slam their doors when entering them through teleporation.

Tilling Blade The island was self-sufficient, and followers tilled the tough soil to grow crops during the warm season.

Survivors suffer from the Blindness, Haemorrhage, and Mangled Status Effects for 80 seconds after becoming injured during Nightfall.

"Like a predatory beast, it can smell and track blood."

Iridescent Wooden Plank Once the journalist's blood stained the wooden boards of the stage, everything was set into motion for The Dredge's arrival.

Survivors suffer from the Exposed Status Effect for the last 12 seconds of Nightfall.

"She came here to poison your minds with fear! Do not let the fear in!" — Otto Stamper

Sacrificial Knife When a journalist attempted to warn the Ottomarians of Stamper's true task, he slit her throat as a warning to any dissenters.

Blocks all Vault locations within 16 metres of the Locker you emerge from for 5 seconds.

"There are imposters amongst you! They intend to destroy our perfect home with dark thoughts. Find them and bring them to me!" — Otto Stamper

Change Log[]

Patch 6.0.2[]

Buff: reduced the Maximum range at which The Dredge is visible during Nightfall from 24 metres to 20 metres.

Nerf: increased the Maximum range at which Survivors are visible to other Survivors during Nightfall from 24 metres to 54 metres.

Patch 8.2.0[]

Buff: increased The Dredge's Movement Speed while charging The Gloaming from 3.68 m/s to 3.8 m/s.

Buff: increased the Daytime Teleportation speed from 12 m/s to 19 m/s.

Buff: reduced the Daytime Teleport cool-down from 12 seconds to 10 seconds.

Buff: reduced the time it takes to break out of a Locked Locker from 3 seconds to 2.25 seconds.

Buff: increased the stack-able Nightfall charging bonus per Injured Survivor from 0.75 c/s to 1.0 c/s.

Buff: reduced the volume of The Dredge's SFX in order to make it harder to detect.

Change: updated several Add-ons.

Trivia[]

The Dredge is the third non-human Killer introduced to Dead by Daylight, acting as a manifestation of the creature Otto Stamper warned his cult-members from.

However, The Dredge is the first non-humanoid Killer, as all previous Killers vaguely resemble a human shape.

The Dredge is the first original non-human character introduced to Dead by Daylight.

The Dredge is the second Killer to have a separate animation when chasing survivors.

The Dredge is the Killer with the highest situational Movement speed in Dead by Daylight, able to move at a maximum of 38 m/s when teleporting during Nightfall.

This disregards instantaneous teleportation Powers, as those are not associated with a Movement speed.

The Dredge is the second Killer to have the pronouns "it" and "its" to refer to it.

This can be attributed to the fact that there is no discernible gender to be assigned to it or to its predecessor in this regard, The Demogorgon .

Despite this, The Dredge has been referred to before with "he/him" pronouns[1].

Lore Trivia[]

The Dredge is described as a Druanee in its Lore, but in real-life mythology, would actually be an "Egregore".

An "Egregore" is an entity described in the Book of Enoch, an ancient Hebrew text, that describes it as "an autonomous psychic entity that is composed of and influencing the thoughts of a group of people", which in Dead by Daylight is the cult led by Otto Stamper.

The Dredge's Lore is heavily intertwined with Otto Stamper, an Unseen Character that was previously mentioned in the Lore of The Doctor , as Stamper was Herman Carter's mentor at Léry's Memorial Institute.

Tome 12 - The Human Quotient, may shed some light on the true origins of the Dredge.

At some point during Talbots journey, he theorises that if enough people worshipped, feared, and thought about a being, it could be brought into existence as a god or demi-god.

His theory seems to have been proven correct by Otto Stamper and the Black Vale.

The name "Fold Energy" also seems to be referenced in the name of the cult itself: "The Fold".

Talbot's theory seems to be based on the idea that Auric Cells can be manipulated by thought, an idea which was also mentioned by Frank Morrison in Tome 3.

Model Trivia[]

The horse head that occasionally drops out of The Dredge's body when idling in the Lobby is "Maurice", The Clown's horse that can be seen on Father Campbell's Chapel.

The Developers reused his asset for The Dredge, deliberately letting Maurice's head fall onto its left side, in order to hide the burnt half of Maurice's head, making it more difficult to recognise him.

As of update 6.5.1, Maurice has been returned to Father Campbells Chapel. The "Memory of Maurice" skin still features the horse head and several others.

The "Skeletal Mass" cosmetic was originally planned to be the default model of The Dredge.

Since every Killer's model is split into three parts for the sake of Cosmetics, The Dredge's rather unusual model causes its splits to be unique.

This also causes the descriptions and names of its Cosmetic Pieces to not match the depicted icons.

The right appendage, holding its weapon, is considered its head piece.

The central amalgam with the "head" is considered its body piece.

The left appendage, acting as both "hand" and "foot", is considered its leg piece. However, the left appendage usually has a description resembling that of the central "body". This can be clearly seen in the anniversary outfit, which calls the left hand a Mask.

Equipping the "Bludgeon of Baubles" Cosmetic grants The Dredge a unique cool-down animation for attacks.

Voice Acting[]

The Dredge has the most accredited voice actors and actresses of any Killer to date, mostly due to its sound design encompassing crowds of wailing souls.

All of the voice actors and actresses are from The Monster Factory and several of them have previously voiced Characters in Dead by Daylight already:

Maude Théberge (previously voiced Lisa Garland)

Sébastien Croteau (previously voiced The Nemesis )

Roxana B.L. (previously voiced The Nemesis' female Zombie)

Vanessa Landry

Misha Standjofski (would go on to voice The Knight )

Philippe Langelier
